📊 GESTOCK - Análisis Exploratorio de Datos¶

Objetivo: Realizar un análisis exploratorio completo de los datos generados para el sistema GESTOCK, identificando patrones, distribuciones y insights iniciales.

Datasets analizados:

  • 🏢 Businesses (8 negocios)
  • 📦 Products (85 productos)
  • 🏭 Warehouses (27 almacenes)
  • 👥 Users (32 usuarios)
  • 📊 Warehouse Products (1,207 registros de stock)
  • 💱 Transactions (1,900 transacciones)

2. Carga de Datos¶

In [22]:
# Cargar todos los datasets
data_path = '../data/raw/'

try:
    # Cargar datasets
    businesses_df = pd.read_csv(f'{data_path}businesses.csv')
    products_df = pd.read_csv(f'{data_path}products.csv')
    warehouses_df = pd.read_csv(f'{data_path}warehouses.csv')
    users_df = pd.read_csv(f'{data_path}users.csv')
    stock_df = pd.read_csv(f'{data_path}warehouse_products.csv')
    transactions_df = pd.read_csv(f'{data_path}transactions.csv')
    
    # Convertir fechas
    businesses_df['created_at'] = pd.to_datetime(businesses_df['created_at'])
    users_df['created_at'] = pd.to_datetime(users_df['created_at'])
    transactions_df['created_at'] = pd.to_datetime(transactions_df['created_at'])
    if 'last_updated' in stock_df.columns:
        stock_df['last_updated'] = pd.to_datetime(stock_df['last_updated'])
    
    print("✅ Datos cargados exitosamente")
    
    # Resumen de datasets
    datasets = {
        'Businesses': len(businesses_df),
        'Products': len(products_df),
        'Warehouses': len(warehouses_df),
        'Users': len(users_df),
        'Stock Records': len(stock_df),
        'Transactions': len(transactions_df)
    }
    
    print("\n📊 RESUMEN DE DATASETS:")
    for dataset, count in datasets.items():
        print(f"  {dataset}: {count:,} registros")
        
except FileNotFoundError as e:
    print(f"❌ Error: {e}")
    print("Asegúrate de haber ejecutado los generadores de datos primero")

# Función para analizar estructura de datasets
def analyze_dataset_structure(df, name):
    print(f"\n{'='*20} {name.upper()} {'='*20}")
    print(f"📐 Dimensiones: {df.shape[0]:,} filas x {df.shape[1]} columnas")
    print(f"\n📋 Columnas:")
    for col in df.columns:
        dtype = df[col].dtype
        null_count = df[col].isnull().sum()
        null_pct = (null_count / len(df)) * 100
        print(f"  {col}: {dtype} (nulos: {null_count} - {null_pct:.1f}%)")
    
    print(f"\n🔍 Preview:")
    display(df.head(3))

# Analizar cada dataset
analyze_dataset_structure(businesses_df, "Businesses")

# Análisis de stock
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))
fig.suptitle('📊 Análisis de Stock', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

# Histograma de stock
axes[0,0].hist(stock_df['stock'], bins=30, color='teal', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
axes[0,0].set_title('Distribución de Stock')
axes[0,0].set_xlabel('Unidades en Stock')
axes[0,0].set_ylabel('Frecuencia')

# Stock por almacén
stock_by_warehouse = stock_df.groupby('warehouse_id')['stock'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
stock_by_warehouse.plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[0,1], color='lightcoral')
axes[0,1].set_title('Stock Total por Almacén')
axes[0,1].set_xlabel('Almacén ID')
axes[0,1].set_ylabel('Stock Total')

# Recrear stock_with_prices con la columna category
stock_with_prices = stock_df.merge(products_df[['id', 'price', 'category']], left_on='product_id', right_on='id')
stock_with_prices['total_value'] = stock_with_prices['stock'] * stock_with_prices['price']

# Valor del inventario por categoría
inventory_by_category = stock_with_prices.groupby('category')['total_value'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
inventory_by_category.plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[1,0], color='mediumseagreen')
axes[1,0].set_title('Valor de Inventario por Categoría')
axes[1,0].set_xlabel('Categoría')
axes[1,0].set_ylabel('Valor ($)')
axes[1,0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

# Top 10 productos por valor en inventario
top_products_value = stock_with_prices.nlargest(10, 'total_value')
axes[1,1].barh(range(len(top_products_value)), top_products_value['total_value'], color='gold')
axes[1,1].set_title('Top 10 Productos por Valor en Inventario')
axes[1,1].set_xlabel('Valor ($)')
axes[1,1].set_yticks(range(len(top_products_value)))
axes[1,1].set_yticklabels([f"Prod {pid}" for pid in top_products_value['product_id']], fontsize=8)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('../reports/images/stock_analysis.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

5. Análisis Temporal de Transacciones¶

5.1 Tendencias Temporales¶

In [35]:
# Preparar datos temporales
transactions_df['date'] = transactions_df['created_at'].dt.date
transactions_df['month'] = transactions_df['created_at'].dt.to_period('M')
transactions_df['weekday'] = transactions_df['created_at'].dt.day_name()
transactions_df['hour'] = transactions_df['created_at'].dt.hour

# Crear visualizaciones temporales
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))
fig.suptitle('📅 Análisis Temporal de Transacciones', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')

# Transacciones por mes
monthly_transactions = transactions_df.groupby(['month', 'type']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)
monthly_transactions.plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[0,0], stacked=True)
axes[0,0].set_title('Transacciones por Mes')
axes[0,0].set_xlabel('Mes')
axes[0,0].set_ylabel('Cantidad')
axes[0,0].legend(title='Tipo')
axes[0,0].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

# Transacciones por día de la semana
weekday_order = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']
weekday_transactions = transactions_df.groupby(['weekday', 'type']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)
weekday_transactions = weekday_transactions.reindex(weekday_order)
weekday_transactions.plot(kind='bar', ax=axes[0,1])
axes[0,1].set_title('Transacciones por Día de la Semana')
axes[0,1].set_xlabel('Día')
axes[0,1].set_ylabel('Cantidad')
axes[0,1].legend(title='Tipo')
axes[0,1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)

# Transacciones por hora
hourly_transactions = transactions_df.groupby('hour').size()
hourly_transactions.plot(kind='line', ax=axes[1,0], marker='o', color='purple')
axes[1,0].set_title('Transacciones por Hora del Día')
axes[1,0].set_xlabel('Hora')
axes[1,0].set_ylabel('Cantidad')
axes[1,0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

# Serie temporal diaria
daily_transactions = transactions_df.groupby('date').size()
daily_transactions.plot(ax=axes[1,1], color='darkgreen')
axes[1,1].set_title('Serie Temporal Diaria')
axes[1,1].set_xlabel('Fecha')
axes[1,1].set_ylabel('Transacciones por Día')
axes[1,1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('../reports/images/temporal_analysis.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

# Estadísticas estacionales
print("📊 ESTADÍSTICAS ESTACIONALES POR CATEGORÍA:")
for category in monthly_category.columns:
    category_data = monthly_category[category]
    peak_month = category_data.idxmax()
    low_month = category_data.idxmin()
    variance = category_data.var()
    print(f"\n{category}:")
    print(f"  📈 Pico: {peak_month} ({category_data.max()} transacciones)")
    print(f"  📉 Mínimo: {low_month} ({category_data.min()} transacciones)")
    print(f"  📊 Varianza: {variance:.1f}")

📊 ESTADÍSTICAS ESTACIONALES POR CATEGORÍA:

Alimentos:
  📈 Pico: 2025-07 (49 transacciones)
  📉 Mínimo: 2025-05 (35 transacciones)

}).round(2)

business_analysis.columns = ['Total_Quantity', 'Total_Transactions', 'Avg_Quantity', 'Entries']
business_analysis['Exits'] = business_analysis['Total_Transactions'] - business_analysis['Entries']
business_analysis['Entry_Ratio'] = (business_analysis['Entries'] / business_analysis['Total_Transactions'] * 100).round(1)

# Agregar información del negocio

business_analysis = business_analysis.join(business_info, how='left')

# Análisis de almacenes
warehouse_analysis = transactions_df.groupby('warehouse_id').agg({
    'quantity': ['sum', 'count', 'mean'],
    'type': lambda x: (x == 'ENTRADA').sum()
}).round(2)

warehouse_analysis.columns = ['Total_Quantity', 'Total_Transactions', 'Avg_Quantity', 'Entries']
warehouse_analysis['Exits'] = warehouse_analysis['Total_Transactions'] - warehouse_analysis['Entries']

# Agregar información del almacén
warehouse_info = warehouses_df[['id', 'name', 'business_id', 'capacity']].set_index('id')
warehouse_analysis = warehouse_analysis.join(warehouse_info, how='left')

# Calcular eficiencia (transacciones por m²)
warehouse_analysis['Efficiency'] = (warehouse_analysis['Total_Transactions'] / warehouse_analysis['capacity']).round(3)

print("📊 CORRELACIONES SIGNIFICATIVAS:")
for i in range(len(correlation_matrix.columns)):
    for j in range(i+1, len(correlation_matrix.columns)):
        corr_value = correlation_matrix.iloc[i, j]
        var1 = correlation_matrix.columns[i]
        var2 = correlation_matrix.columns[j]
        print(f"  {var1} vs {var2}: {corr_value:.3f}")
